canonical:
  title: 賜任元厚授門下侍郞同中書門下平章事
  author: 郭東珣
  language: lzh
  text: 天官天爵天下之公器可以與賢者共之不可私於人也卿寬厚有長者之風而動靜得大臣之體自作而行事之時至坐而論道之日厥有成績卓爲宗工予其申錫異恩以觀來効玆所以採搢紳中外之公論非朕私於卿也
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賜任元厚授門下侍郞同中書門下平章事
  author: 郭東珣
  language: lzh
  text: 天官天爵。天下之公器。可以與賢者共之。不可私於人也。卿寬厚有長者之風。而動靜得大臣之體。自作而行事之時。至坐而論道之日。厥有成績。卓爲宗工。予其申錫異恩。以觀來効。玆所以採搢紳中外之公論。非朕私於卿也。
korean:
  title: 사 임원후 수 문하시랑 동중서 문하평장사
  author: 곽동순
  language: kor
  text: 천관(天官)과 천작(天爵)은 천하의 공기(公器)니, 어진 자와 더불어 함께 할 수 있는 것이요, 사사로운 정으로 다른 사람에게 줄 수는 없는 것이다. 경은 관후하여 장자의 풍도가 있고 동정(動靜)은 대신의 체통을 얻었다. 등용되어 일을 행하던 때로부터 앉아서 도를 의논하는 날에 이르기까지 많은 공적이 있어서 탁월한 종공(宗工)이 되었다. 그러므로 나는 남다른 은혜를 거듭 내리어 장래의 공효를 보려 한다. 이것은 안팎 사대부들의 공론에 의한 것이며, 내가 사사로운 정으로 경에게 주는 것이 아니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0280_010_0080&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: On the Appointment of Im Won-hou as Attendant Official of the Chancellery and Minister of the Combined Secretariat
  author: Gwak Dong-sun
  language: eng
  text: Heaven's offices and Heaven's ranks are the common instruments of all under Heaven—to be shared with the worthy, never bestowed through private favor. You possess a generous and magnanimous spirit, bearing the manner of an elder statesman. In motion and in stillness alike, you embody the bearing of a great minister. From the day you were appointed to conduct affairs, through to this hour when you sit to discuss the Way, your achievements have been manifest. You have become eminent as a master of tradition. Thus I bestow upon you this singular grace, to observe your service in times to come. This comes not from my private preference, but from the considered judgment of the scholars and ministers both within and without the realm.
  footnotes:
    - The phrase 'Heaven's offices and Heaven's ranks' (天官天爵) refers to positions of government bestowed according to merit and virtue, a concept emphasizing that such appointments are not personal privileges but public trusts.
    - '''Master of tradition'' (宗工) indicates one who has become exemplary in governance and moral conduct, setting a standard for others to follow.'
